    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved pan to a medium heat with the <strong>sliced onion</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 4-5 min or until beginning to soften</p><p>Slice your <strong>chestnut mushrooms</strong> finely, then chop your <strong>creamed coconut </strong>roughly (if required!)</p><p>Dissolve your <strong>chicken stock mix</strong>, <strong>sriracha </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!), 1/2 tsp<span class=\"text-purple\"> [3/4 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[1 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong> and the <strong>chopped creamed coconut</strong> in 600ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[900ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[1.2L]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>– this is your <strong>coconut stock</strong></p>",
