    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the onion has softened, add the <strong>chopped lemongrass inner core</strong>, <strong>chopped ginger</strong>, <strong>sliced mushrooms</strong> and your <strong>chilli flakes </strong>(not a fan of spice? Just add a little!) to the pan and cook for 1 min</p><p>Add the<strong> coconut stock</strong> with the <strong>browned</strong> <strong>chicken thighs</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium-high and cook, covered, for 10 min or until the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!)</p>",
